Description: Granodiorite column in the form of a papyrus bundle bearing cartouches of Amenhotep III, Merenptah and Setnakht on abacus, buds and shaft.
Curator's comments: Published Kitchen, Ram. Insc. Vol 4 p.52 / Vol 5 p.3 Published: HTBM Part 9: Plate II
Bibliographic references: James 1970 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc., in the British Museum, Part 9. (Pl.2)
